- Don't go, V.

15:21.130 --> 15:23.089
I'm serious.
Learn from my stupid mistake.

15:23.089 --> 15:27.094
As members of this community,
we encourage you to join

15:27.094 --> 15:28.887
for just a $2,000 buy-in.

15:28.887 --> 15:30.221
That'll cover the cost

15:30.221 --> 15:32.807
of the plots, the fence,
the irrigation system,

15:32.807 --> 15:35.060
- And the chicken coop.
- Wow, just $2,000?

15:35.060 --> 15:39.272
Yeah. Sadly, your aboveground
pool will have to go.

15:39.272 --> 15:41.566
But, hey, it's fall.

15:41.566 --> 15:43.568
You won't need it
till next summer, so...

15:43.568 --> 15:48.156
thanks for taking it down.
Okay. Good--good talk.

15:48.156 --> 15:50.117
This neighborhood
has gone to shit.

15:50.117 --> 15:51.326
Right?

15:58.917 --> 16:00.919
Check it out.
My boss gave me a shit ton

16:00.919 --> 16:02.420
of drugs to take
on a bus to Michigan.

16:02.420 --> 16:05.090
Oh, my god.

16:05.090 --> 16:08.843
- You really improved at math.
- No, somebody got shot.

16:08.843 --> 16:11.054
- Give your old man a taste.
- I will if you come with me.

16:11.054 --> 16:13.098
But you got to buy
your bus ticket.

16:13.098 --> 16:15.308
Dad, your pills.

16:15.308 --> 16:18.686
Oh, thank you, dear.

16:18.686 --> 16:23.108
Listen, uh, I was thinking
of taking a little field trip

16:23.108 --> 16:24.359
with young Carl
this afternoon.

16:24.359 --> 16:27.071
Get in some father-son bonding.

16:27.071 --> 16:30.115
Oh, that's a nice idea...

16:30.115 --> 16:32.159
for tomorrow.

16:32.159 --> 16:34.494
But today we've got to
go to the hospital

16:34.494 --> 16:35.870
to get your wound checked,

16:35.870 --> 16:38.123
and I promised Chuckie
that after that,

16:38.123 --> 16:42.211
you'll teach him to toss
a ball with your good arm.

16:45.630 --> 16:48.007
Uh, of course.
That's a better plan.

16:48.007 --> 16:51.928
Good.
All right.

16:51.928 --> 16:53.930
Hop to.

17:02.105 --> 17:05.984
Put the drugs on Chuckie.
Just strap him up.

17:05.984 --> 17:07.527
Why?

17:07.527 --> 17:09.654
Because you're 14,
you look like a criminal,

17:09.654 --> 17:11.739
the cops can spot
you a mile off,

17:11.739 --> 17:14.534
while Chuckie--they take
one look at that mongoloid,

17:14.534 --> 17:16.619
and all they want
to do is look away.

17:16.619 --> 17:19.330
Here.

17:19.330 --> 17:21.749
Buy him a bus ticket.

17:21.749 --> 17:23.126
Yeah?

17:23.126 --> 17:25.753
And give your old man
a taste for the effort.

17:25.753 --> 17:30.300
[cell phone ringing]

17:41.644 --> 17:44.647
Ian's bipolar
with psychosis.

17:44.647 --> 17:47.025
You knew that
already, right?

17:47.025 --> 17:49.153
Knowing it and having
a lifelong diagnosis

17:49.153 --> 17:51.571
are two very
different things.

17:51.571 --> 17:53.156
Got it. Sorry.

17:53.156 --> 17:55.242
Meanwhile, Gus
is going on tour

17:55.242 --> 17:57.285
for I don't even know how long,
and apparently that means

17:57.285 --> 18:00.205
he's gonna fuck groupies
in every state.

18:00.205 --> 18:02.207
- He said that?
- No, 'cause he hasn't said

18:02.207 --> 18:05.127
more than ten words to me
in three days.

18:05.127 --> 18:08.213
In fairness to him, that is
my fucking fault, but still.

18:08.213 --> 18:10.298
He's giving you that cold,
silent thing.

18:10.298 --> 18:12.134
Yeah. And I don't know
what to do with that.

18:12.134 --> 18:14.136
I keep waiting
for the fight-and-fuck.

18:14.136 --> 18:16.304
- The what?
- You know, the big fight--

18:16.304 --> 18:18.932
blood, tears, screaming--
and then you fuck,

18:18.932 --> 18:21.351
and then it's over.
But Gus isn't like that.

18:21.351 --> 18:24.313
And with this silent thing,
it's, like, never over.

18:24.313 --> 18:26.231
Usually the silent thing
from a guy means it's over

18:26.231 --> 18:28.900
and he hasn't told you yet.

18:28.900 --> 18:32.362
- The fight?
- No, the marriage.

18:32.362 --> 18:34.781
You have not told him that
you don't want him to go?

18:34.781 --> 18:38.034
No, I was giving
him space.

18:38.034 --> 18:39.911
Speaking as somebody
who's sabotaged

18:39.911 --> 18:42.914
more than one marriage,
I'm not sure space is what

18:42.914 --> 18:45.083
he needs from you
right now.

18:45.083 --> 18:46.876
Groveling might be
a better idea.

18:46.876 --> 18:48.503
- [scoffs]
- You think I'm kidding?

18:48.503 --> 18:52.423
I'm not.
You should beg him like a dog.

18:52.423 --> 18:54.175
Beg him not to go.

18:54.175 --> 18:57.428
- I got tables.
- Okay, it's your divorce.

18:57.428 --> 18:59.764
[scoffs] You're kind of
a dick, you know that?

18:59.764 --> 19:02.225
Yeah.
Have we met?

19:15.071 --> 19:18.283
Asshead, get in.

19:18.283 --> 19:21.119
I thought you said
we were going to play catch.

19:26.624 --> 19:28.376
What's in those bags, Carl?

19:28.376 --> 19:30.670
Horse.

19:30.670 --> 19:32.213
Why are you taping horse
to my tummy?

19:32.213 --> 19:35.342
Because I'm your uncle
and your my niece.

19:35.342 --> 19:36.509
And you do what I say.

19:36.509 --> 19:38.303
I think you mean nephew.

19:38.303 --> 19:39.887
I think I mean keep
your mouth shut

19:39.887 --> 19:42.098
and keep it shut
no matter what,

19:42.098 --> 19:44.309
and don't tell anyone
a word about this,

19:44.309 --> 19:46.352
or else I'll tie a fucking
tire around your tummy

19:46.352 --> 19:49.647
and set it on fire,
even if you are my niece.

19:49.647 --> 19:52.276
Okay, uncle Carl.

20:22.764 --> 20:25.767
[psychedelic rock music]

20:25.767 --> 20:33.775
