20:51.584 --> 20:53.211
Which one's your room?

20:53.211 --> 20:54.629
I'm not going
to my room.

20:54.629 --> 20:57.215
Too many drop-ins.

20:57.215 --> 21:00.468
Kid attempted suicide
in this room, so it's empty.

21:00.468 --> 21:04.263
We can set up
shop in here.

21:04.263 --> 21:07.308
Oh, yeah, the kid weighed,
like, 320 pounds.

21:07.308 --> 21:09.268
He tried to hang himself.

21:09.268 --> 21:10.853
I think it was more
of a cry for help

21:10.853 --> 21:13.564
than an actual
attempt, though.

21:13.564 --> 21:16.359
I know it sounds depressing,
but, you know,

21:16.359 --> 21:19.570
really, the kid just got some
bruises on his fourth chin.

21:19.570 --> 21:22.573
No, no, no, no.
It's just--

21:22.573 --> 21:25.827
I miss my girls,
you know, that's it.

21:25.827 --> 21:27.496
Hey, do you mind
if I call 'em?

21:27.496 --> 21:30.499
Yeah, go for it.
Do your thing.

21:31.457 --> 21:34.336
[phone ringing]

21:34.336 --> 21:36.504
- Da?
- Hey, Svet, it's Kev.

21:36.504 --> 21:37.839
How they doing?

21:37.839 --> 21:39.465
They are napping
with Veronica.

21:39.465 --> 21:41.300
Great.
It's good, isn't it?

21:41.300 --> 21:43.511
Yeah. It's possible she give
them vodka to help sleep,

21:43.511 --> 21:45.638
but worse things
happen in world.

21:45.638 --> 21:48.975
Yah. Listen, I'm gonna be
gone most of the day

21:48.975 --> 21:54.188
and, uh, maybe tonight, so can
you help out V in any way?

21:54.188 --> 21:55.523
And also tell her that I need
her to cover the bar

21:55.523 --> 21:56.524
for me tonight?

21:56.524 --> 21:58.484
Cover bar with babies?

21:58.484 --> 22:00.319
Oh, god. Maybe I should just
check on it

22:00.319 --> 22:01.320
and have Debbie babysit.

22:01.320 --> 22:03.239
Ah, it's okay.
I babysit.

22:03.239 --> 22:05.658
(Kev)
Oh, Svet, thank--

22:07.577 --> 22:09.538
You okay?

22:09.538 --> 22:11.914
Yeah.
Just uh--

22:11.914 --> 22:13.542
Well, hey, can you, uh,

22:13.542 --> 22:16.085
be sad and roll joints
at the same time?

22:16.085 --> 22:18.337
There's 18 frats
on this campus.

22:18.337 --> 22:19.505
I want to hit 'em all.

22:19.505 --> 22:22.509
Where are we going?

22:22.509 --> 22:23.968
Michigan.

22:23.968 --> 22:25.970
- When will we be back?
- Tonight.

22:29.849 --> 22:31.476
I miss my mom.

22:31.476 --> 22:32.518
Be a good little niece,
and there's more

22:32.518 --> 22:34.979
junk food where
that came from.

22:39.859 --> 22:43.696
[dog barking]

22:47.074 --> 22:49.368
You alone?

22:49.368 --> 22:50.828
Uncle Carl?

22:50.828 --> 22:53.164
[dogs barking]

22:53.164 --> 22:54.582
Sorry about that.

22:54.582 --> 22:57.627
This new liver
really churns 'em out--

22:57.627 --> 23:00.547
three craps a day,
like I'm 18 again.

23:00.547 --> 23:04.175
That's good, dad--
healthy.

23:04.175 --> 23:08.638
But why don't we cover
your ass while we wait, huh?

23:08.638 --> 23:11.516
Hey.

23:11.516 --> 23:13.434
Frequent flier Frank.

23:13.434 --> 23:16.521
- What's that?
- You. Frequent flier Frank.

23:16.521 --> 23:17.939
You're a bit of a legend
around these parts.

23:17.939 --> 23:19.982
Honor to finally meet you.

23:19.982 --> 23:22.318
I sense sarcasm.

23:22.318 --> 23:24.403
I smell infection.

23:24.403 --> 23:25.947
Mm.

23:25.947 --> 23:28.157
Have you been cleaning
this regularly?

23:28.157 --> 23:31.702
I have, but he had
a liver transplant last year

23:31.702 --> 23:33.913
and with the antirejection
meds, his healing process

23:33.913 --> 23:35.457
has been a little wonky.

23:35.457 --> 23:37.584
Got it.
How'd you get shot?

23:37.584 --> 23:41.921
He was cleaning his gun,
and it backfired.

23:41.921 --> 23:45.383
He was cleaning his gun, and
it backfired into his outer arm?

23:45.383 --> 23:47.844
Uh-huh.

23:47.844 --> 23:52.056
You sure about
that story, Frank?

23:52.056 --> 23:54.559
- He is.
- I am.

23:54.559 --> 23:56.686
As a matter of fact,
I'm glad it happened,

23:56.686 --> 23:59.897
because Sammi is such
a good caregiver,

23:59.897 --> 24:01.649
and it affords me
extra time with her.

24:01.649 --> 24:05.194
You see, I missed the first
30-some-odd years of her life,

24:05.194 --> 24:07.572
and I think I can safely say

24:07.572 --> 24:10.950
we both enjoy me being hurt.

24:14.495 --> 24:17.373
Aww.

24:17.373 --> 24:19.041
Daddy.

24:22.712 --> 24:25.339
Mm.

24:27.717 --> 24:30.595
[moaning]
Oh, Kev.

24:30.595 --> 24:32.305
Oh, my--

24:32.305 --> 24:34.683
[gasps]

24:34.683 --> 24:37.476
Uh...

24:37.476 --> 24:40.646
What the--
What the fuck?

24:40.646 --> 24:43.649
I cook, I clean,
wifely duties.

24:43.649 --> 24:46.277
You are landlord.
I am tenant.

24:46.277 --> 24:48.279
Uh, are you kidding?
I'm not gay.

24:48.279 --> 24:50.239
Ah, what is gay?
This is not about love.

24:50.239 --> 24:51.658
This is about
oral manipulation

24:51.658 --> 24:53.535
of sex organs
as stress relief.

24:53.535 --> 24:55.662
No stress is good
for bond with babies.

24:55.662 --> 24:58.664
Tongue is tongue, no?

24:58.664 --> 25:02.418
What the hell?
I'm halfway home already.

25:02.418 --> 25:04.671
♪ Hey all you kooky kids
out there ♪

25:04.671 --> 25:09.467
♪ Get down
to the dizzy x sound ♪

25:09.467 --> 25:13.179
[all cheering]

25:13.179 --> 25:16.849
[all chanting "Drink!"]

25:16.849 --> 25:24.649
