a holiday come ♪

25:51.634 --> 25:53.928
Ian!

25:53.928 --> 25:55.179
Ian?

25:59.892 --> 26:03.229
Hey, there.
Uh, Ian, isn't it?

26:03.229 --> 26:05.272
I remember that 'cause
that's my therapist's name,

26:05.272 --> 26:07.817
and he's a ginger too.
[chuckles]

26:07.817 --> 26:11.570
Anyway, uh, I was wondering
when you think

26:11.570 --> 26:16.325
you might be able to get
to taking down this pool.

26:16.325 --> 26:19.704
Mm, well...

26:19.704 --> 26:23.958
I'm coming down off some
heavy lithium right now...

26:23.958 --> 26:27.796
but maybe
in an hour or two.

26:27.796 --> 26:30.131
Perfect.

26:30.131 --> 26:33.092
(Debbie)
Ian!

26:33.092 --> 26:36.095
Oh, my god,
there you are.

26:36.095 --> 26:37.555
Here I am.

26:37.555 --> 26:39.974
Ian, what happened
to all your pills?

26:39.974 --> 26:41.642
They're gone.

26:41.642 --> 26:43.477
Yeah, I-I can see that
they're gone, but gone where?

26:43.477 --> 26:45.647
Did you swallow them?

26:45.647 --> 26:49.734
No. They're flushed.

26:49.734 --> 26:51.694
Ian, why would you
do that?

26:54.822 --> 26:56.782
They make me
feel awful, Debs,

26:56.782 --> 26:59.702
like life is not
worth living.

26:59.702 --> 27:02.496
I feel so much better
just knowing they're gone.

27:05.916 --> 27:08.044
You know what I find
really moving, Sammi?

27:08.044 --> 27:10.171
The way you love
that boy of yours.

27:10.171 --> 27:12.923
- You messing with me?
- No.

27:12.923 --> 27:16.761
No, my Monica didn't have
much interest in our brood.

27:16.761 --> 27:19.513
Her love was transient
at best--fickle.

27:19.513 --> 27:22.433
Fact is, she left us
high and dry.

27:22.433 --> 27:25.019
But the way you
are with Chuckie,

27:25.019 --> 27:27.688
he's the center of your world,
and you'd never leave him.

27:27.688 --> 27:30.232
I-I find that...

27:30.232 --> 27:32.693
inspiring, sincerely.

27:32.693 --> 27:34.779
Thanks. Dad...
[cell phone ringing]

27:34.779 --> 27:37.114
That means a lot.

27:39.992 --> 27:43.537
Hello?

27:43.537 --> 27:46.040
What?

27:46.040 --> 27:47.249
Wait.

27:47.249 --> 27:51.212
Who--who is?
What?

27:51.212 --> 27:52.839
He was what?

27:52.839 --> 27:55.633
I'd like to make
a concerned citizen report

27:55.633 --> 27:58.803
about a large satchel
filled with hard drugs.

27:58.803 --> 28:02.724
N-n-no, I demand
a lawyer. I--

28:02.724 --> 28:06.227
I demand you stop
questioning him right now!

28:06.227 --> 28:08.855
Wait--wait. I'm coming.
Let me talk to Chuckie!

28:08.855 --> 28:10.147
Put Chuckie on the
god damn phone right now.

28:10.147 --> 28:11.649
There's some sort of
an emergency.

28:14.902 --> 28:17.905
You really think I can
ask him not to go on tour?

28:17.905 --> 28:20.742
- No.
- Then why'd you suggest it?

28:20.742 --> 28:22.993
Because I'm trying to hasten
the end of this thing

28:22.993 --> 28:25.914
you're calling a marriage.

28:25.914 --> 28:27.957
I can't tell if
you're kidding or not.

28:27.957 --> 28:30.751
Yeah.
Neither can I.

28:30.751 --> 28:33.462
- I'm asking for your advice.
- Yeah, I know.

28:33.462 --> 28:36.590
But it's
complicated for me.

28:36.590 --> 28:38.592
Wait. You're the one
that said we couldn't--

28:38.592 --> 28:42.806
Yeah, I know. I'm, um--I'm
just calling a spade a spade.

28:42.806 --> 28:45.683
You need to decide
what you want here.

28:45.683 --> 28:48.102
- With you?
- With your husband. Keep up.

28:48.102 --> 28:49.854
I'm trying.

28:49.854 --> 28:52.231
Okay, walking on eggshells and
sitting around feeling guilty

28:52.231 --> 28:53.774
isn't a decision.
You need to make a decision.

28:53.774 --> 28:55.317
I told him what I did.

28:55.317 --> 28:56.819
I told him I was sorry.
I sent Jimmy away.

28:56.819 --> 28:58.529
What the fuck else
am I supposed to do?

28:58.529 --> 29:01.115
You're scrappy, Fiona.
You know how to fight.

29:01.115 --> 29:03.576
Don't pretend you don't
know how to fight.

29:03.576 --> 29:05.494
- So?
- So either fight

29:05.494 --> 29:06.871
for this marriage
or cut him loose.

29:06.871 --> 29:08.289
Let him lick his wounds
and move on.

29:08.289 --> 29:10.082
You know, this halfway thing
you're doing,

29:10.082 --> 29:13.502
giving him space,
is kind of fucked, right?

29:13.502 --> 29:14.921
If this is a relationship
you want to save,

29:14.921 --> 29:17.047
then you got
to fucking save it.

29:17.047 --> 29:19.801
- Fiona?
- Hey. You okay?

29:19.801 --> 29:21.093
- I'm sorry.

29:21.093 --> 29:23.095
It's all my fault.
I'm so sorry.

29:23.095 --> 29:24.680
What happened?

29:24.680 --> 29:27.016
He flushed his pills.

29:27.016 --> 29:32.730
- 37, 50, 750,
1, 2, 3, 4, 5.

29:33.982 --> 29:37.861
That's $756.
[clears throat]

29:37.861 --> 29:40.779
Your outstanding bill
is still over $6,000.

29:40.779 --> 29:43.949
I know, and I'll keep
making the payments.

29:43.949 --> 29:45.826
It's unusual for us
to take payments in cash.

29:45.826 --> 29:48.662
Honestly, it's unusual for
us to take payments at all.

29:48.662 --> 29:50.122
Yeah. No, I get that,
and I, uh--

29:50.122 --> 29:51.916
you know, I really,
really appreciate

29:51.916 --> 29:53.709
your patience with me.

29:53.709 --> 29:54.961
Phillip--

29:54.961 --> 29:56.879
It's, uh, lip.

29:56.879 --> 29:58.464
I figure I-I'm gonna
be here a lot.

29:58.464 --> 30:01.592
We might as well
get to know one another.

30:01.592 --> 30:04.971
Lip, have you considered
taking a semester off,

30:04.971 --> 30:06.722
working and saving
your money?

30:06.722 --> 30:07.806
You can come back
next semester

30:07.806 --> 30:09.725
with your financial aid
paperwork intact

30:09.725 --> 30:11.019
and maybe have a little
extra spending money

30:11.019 --> 30:12.311
in your pocket, instead--

30:12.311 --> 30:16.232
I won't make it back.

30:16.232 --> 30:18.984
My, uh...

30:18.984 --> 30:23.239
my little brother Ian
was just diagnosed bipolar.

30:23.239 --> 30:25.616
You know, and--and every
day I'm here, I ju--

30:25.616 --> 30:28.870
I feel so fucking guilty,
you know,

30:28.870 --> 30:31.747
that I'm not there helping.

30:33.749 --> 30:36.044
You know, and the
only reason I-I stay

30:36.044 --> 30:39.463
is, uh...

30:39.463 --> 30:43.717
you know, I can't help.

30:43.717 --> 30:47.055
Yeah, look, 'cause I
spent my whole life,

30:47.055 --> 30:49.473
uh, trying to help my--

30:49.473 --> 30:51.517
my mom, um...

30:51.517 --> 30:55.479
you know,
has the same disease.

30:55.479 --> 30:58.107
And there's no
help for it...

31:00.651 --> 31:02.861
You know, except the--
the little ones, uh, Debbie

31:02.861 --> 31:04.947
and, uh, and--and Carl
and--and Liam

31:04.947 --> 31:06.407
and my sister Fiona.

31:06.407 --> 31:08.534
You know, I-I could be
there for them,

31:08.534 --> 31:11.036
but I'm not...

31:11.036 --> 31:14.581
you know,
'cause I'm here...

31:14.581 --> 31:17.835
'cause I'm told that--that
staying here,

31:17.835 --> 31:19.628
you know, that's--that's
something I could do

31:19.628 --> 31:21.714
for those kids, you know,
in--in a big way.

31:21.714 --> 31:26.051
You know, in--in a real
way, uh, someday.

31:26.051 --> 31:28.512
So I'm here.

31:32.016 --> 31:35.602
But if I go back
to the house...

31:35.602 --> 31:37.187
well, then I'm in it,

31:37.187 --> 31:40.524
you know, and--and I can't
get back out of it.

31:42.944 --> 31:45.029
You know, so I'm--I'm
gonna keep coming here,

31:45.029 --> 31:48.115
and I'm--I'm gonna keep, uh,
making these payments.

31:48.115 --> 31:50.076
I'm gonna--I'm gonna show up,
and I'm gonna count 'em out,

31:50.076 --> 31:51.493
and then, you know,
that'll be my part.

31:51.493 --> 31:54.580
And your part,
I hope, is, um...

31:56.123 --> 31:58.125
patience.

32:00.919 --> 32:02.796
Please, you know,
I just...

32:04.840 --> 32:07.135
Fuck, I just need
a little time.

32:12.015 --> 32:15.100
One more week
is all I can do.

32:15.100 --> 32:18.645
You need a prescription
for a refill.

32:18.645 --> 32:21.148
I understand that that's
officially true.

32:21.148 --> 32:23.150
But you know that these
prescriptions are only written

32:23.150 --> 32:24.777
for people who do
crazy shit,

32:24.777 --> 32:26.362
like flush their meds
down the toilet

32:26.362 --> 32:27.905
'cause they don't want
to take them,

32:27.905 --> 32:29.740
so maybe you can just
refill them

32:29.740 --> 32:30.949
'cause you know
it's the right thing to do

32:30.949 --> 32:33.995
instead of giving us
the official line.

32:33.995 --> 32:37.122
Officially, I will go
to jail if I do that.

32:37.122 --> 32:41.460
Get a prescription,
and you can have a refill.

32:41.460 --> 32:45.339
Come on.
Come on.

32:49.385 --> 32:51.512
When did you fall
in love with yours?

32:51.512 --> 32:54.515
There was no falling,
just being.

32:54.515 --> 32:56.184
He comes out,
they hand him to me,

32:56.184 --> 32:57.351
everything changes.

32:57.351 --> 32:59.603
Before Yevgeny,
I was selfish.

32:59.603 --> 33:01.980
Now I would die
before I let him die.

33:01.980 --> 33:06.110
It's simple, complete.

33:06.110 --> 33:08.320
I never made that change.

33:08.320 --> 33:10.155
Kev did.
I didn't.

33:10.155 --> 33:12.366
Some do, some don't.

33:12.366 --> 33:16.162
I hate him for changing,
and he hates me for not.

33:16.162 --> 33:18.914
Because you Americans like
everything to be right or wrong.

33:18.914 --> 33:20.582
If someone is like you,
it is right.

33:20.582 --> 33:22.876
If someone is not,
it is wrong.

33:22.876 --> 33:24.503
But this is not real.

33:24.503 --> 33:28.216
Life is not so this or that,
black and white.

33:28.216 --> 33:31.093
No, you should be happy your
Kev makes these changes,

33:31.093 --> 33:34.805
because if no one does, this is
how babies end up in dumpsters.

33:38.851 --> 33:40.436
I don't give a shit
about Chuckie,

33:40.436 --> 33:42.188
but I'm pretty sure
G-Dogg's gonna kill me.

33:42.188 --> 33:44.148
No, he won't.
There's nothing to be gained

33:44.148 --> 33:47.401
by killing a perfectly
good corner boy.

33:47.401 --> 33:50.446
And it's not your fault that
they came with drug dogs.

33:50.446 --> 33:53.407
That's the luck of the draw.
G-Dogg will understand that.

33:53.407 --> 33:55.993
You really think so?

33:55.993 --> 33:58.036
I'm almost certain.

33:58.036 --> 34:00.998
I'm fucked.
What should I do about Sammi?

34:00.998 --> 34:01.999
Should I run away?

34:01.999 --> 34:03.208
No, it makes you
look guilty.

34:03.208 --> 34:05.836
Stay here, stay cool,
let the storm pass.

34:07.963 --> 34:09.339
(Debbie)
He's not gonna listen.

34:09.339 --> 34:11.383
Well, it doesn't mean
I can't talk.

34:11.383 --> 34:13.051
We need to get meds
and crush 'em up

34:13.051 --> 34:15.221
and put 'em in his food,
like, in a smoothie.

34:15.221 --> 34:17.723
Well, let's let that
be plan "b."

34:17.723 --> 34:20.601
- Where is he?
- Backyard, I think.

34:20.601 --> 34:22.352
- All right.

34:30.110 --> 34:33.906
Flushed your pills?

34:33.906 --> 34:36.992
You get that that's a
full-on Monica move, right?

34:36.992 --> 34:39.411
- I'm not Monica.
- Come on.

34:39.411 --> 34:40.871
Let's go to the clinic.

34:40.871 --> 34:42.372
Let's get you
a new prescription.

34:42.372 --> 34:44.374
No.

34:46.376 --> 34:48.378
Debbie feels like it's her
fault 'cause I left her in ch--

34:48.378 --> 34:49.838
Now you're trying
to manipulate me

34:49.838 --> 34:52.300
like we used to do
with Monica.

34:52.300 --> 34:54.218
- Ian--
- I'm not Monica.

34:54.218 --> 34:57.387
I didn't slash my wrists
over Thanksgiving dinner.

34:57.387 --> 34:59.264
- I went for a drive.
- You took a baby.

34:59.264 --> 35:02.434
I took him...

35:02.434 --> 35:06.271
For a drive, and, yeah, I guess
it was a really long drive,

35:06.271 --> 35:08.065
and I didn't plan ahead...

35:08.065 --> 35:11.194
but I did not hurt
that baby.

35:11.194 --> 35:13.445
I took care of the baby.
I fed the baby.

35:13.445 --> 35:18.201
I sang to the baby.
I love that baby.

35:18.201 --> 35:19.826
I get why everyone's
freaking out,

35:19.826 --> 35:21.662
but, I mean, you pulled
some pretty serious shit

35:21.662 --> 35:25.290
not too long ago and everyone
didn't try to turn on you

35:25.290 --> 35:27.000
and permanently
medicate you.

35:27.000 --> 35:31.255
- I went to jail.
- So did I.

35:31.255 --> 35:32.881
And now I'm out.

35:32.881 --> 35:36.051
I'm not Monica
any more than you are.

35:37.386 --> 35:39.846
[rock music playing on TV]

35:39.846 --> 35:42.308
Debs?

35:44.185 --> 35:45.769
Debs?
Where's Debbie?

35:45.769 --> 35:49.147
She said something about
going out to buy drugs.

35:49.147 --> 35:51.441
Are you serious?
You couldn't stop her?

35:51.441 --> 35:53.068
I'm injured.

35:53.068 --> 35:55.862
Besides, it'd be
a little hypocritical.

36:04.705 --> 36:08.709
[music stops, dragon roars]

36:08.709 --> 36:12.504
- Debs!
- So strident.

36:12.504 --> 36:14.840
Debbie!

36:14.840 --> 36:16.717
Oh, God damn it.
Debs!

36:16.717 --> 36:18.302
Hey.
What's going on?

36:18.302 --> 36:21.138
What is not going on?
Everything is fucked.

36:21.138 --> 36:22.848
Why are you
dressed like that?

36:22.848 --> 36:24.975
I told you,
I have a date.

36:24.975 --> 36:27.477
And I told you not
to fuck up your life.

36:27.477 --> 36:29.354
I'm not kidding.
I'm serious, V.

36:29.354 --> 36:32.358
Do not fucking do that.
You guys are happy.

36:32.358 --> 36:35.235
And you can be happy again, but
not if you go fuck someone else.

36:35.235 --> 36:39.072
And the two of you--
I mean, I can't handle it

36:39.072 --> 36:40.866
if you can't figure
this shit out, okay?

36:40.866 --> 36:43.118
And--and maybe that's
not fucking fair,

36:43.118 --> 36:45.287
but you guys--
you're Kev and V.

36:45.287 --> 36:46.955
So figure it out.

36:46.955 --> 36:48.915
It's not fair.

36:48.915 --> 36:50.959
Fine.

36:50.959 --> 36:52.502
You're married too,
Fiona.

36:52.502 --> 36:54.630
And you were happy too,
and then you fucked Jimmy.

36:54.630 --> 36:58.300
So figure out your own shit
instead of putting it all on me.

37:00.427 --> 37:02.846
Fine. Fuck.

37:05.308 --> 37:08.060
I'm sorry.

37:39.633 --> 37:41.551
- What?
- Mickey here?

37:41.551 --> 37:44.554
[electric guitar rock]

37:44.554 --> 37:49.226
♪ ♪

37:49.226 --> 37:50.519
Ian fucking sent you?

37:50.519 --> 37:52.270
No, Ian didn't send me.

37:52.270 --> 37:55.482
Ian flushed all his meds
down the freakin' toilet.

37:55.482 --> 37:58.276
What happened to your face?

37:58.276 --> 38:00.404
Nothing.
What the fuck do you want?

38:00.404 --> 38:02.197
Can you help me
get these drugs?

38:02.197 --> 38:05.492
♪ ♪

38:05.492 --> 38:07.411
Iggy!

38:07.411 --> 38:09.121
Iggy!

38:09.121 --> 38:11.415
Can you get that shit?

38:11.415 --> 38:13.375
Who the fuck gets high
on lithium?

38:13.375 --> 38:15.293
- No one.
- So?

38:15.293 --> 38:17.379
So I can't get 'em.

38:17.379 --> 38:20.132
I can get you crack,
crystal, horse, "e."

38:20.132 --> 38:22.759
But this shit, no.
There's no market for it.

38:22.759 --> 38:24.428
I'll take some
fucking crack.

38:24.428 --> 38:26.304
You got money?

38:26.304 --> 38:28.432
♪ ♪

38:28.432 --> 38:31.393
Fine. When are you gonna
come by to see Ian?

38:31.393 --> 38:32.978
He's been home all day.

38:32.978 --> 38:34.896
- Maybe if you were there--
- [belches]

38:34.896 --> 38:36.898
Did you guys break up
or something?

38:36.898 --> 38:39.402
Because I'm pretty sure he
didn't mean to kidnap your baby.

38:39.402 --> 38:41.445
I'm fucking busy,
Peppermint Patty.

38:41.445 --> 38:44.114
Go whine at someone
who gives a shit.

38:44.114 --> 38:46.450
♪ ♪

38:46.450 --> 38:47.617
[music stops]

38:51.539 --> 38:54.207
Frank used to drink
like this.

38:54.207 --> 38:56.418
When Monica was around
and they would fight,

38:56.418 --> 38:59.129
he would angry drink.

38:59.129 --> 39:00.839
It never worked.

39:00.839 --> 39:03.384
He always came back
to her.

39:03.384 --> 39:05.511
You can't drink him away,
Mickey.

39:05.511 --> 39:07.637
It won't work.

39:23.695 --> 39:26.865
- Veronica Fisher.
- Hey.

39:26.865 --> 39:29.075
- You look fine, girl.
- Thank you, Eddie.

39:29.075 --> 39:30.452
You look...yeah.

39:30.452 --> 39:31.620
[both chuckle]

39:31.620 --> 39:34.540
Mmm...

39:35.957 --> 39:38.126
Damn, Princess,
how long has it been?

39:38.126 --> 39:40.463
Long time.

39:40.463 --> 39:42.422
Those lips feel
like yesterday.

39:42.422 --> 39:46.343
Should we sit, or should we
find someplace more private?

39:50.138 --> 39:51.431
I'm sorry, Eddie.

39:51.431 --> 39:54.518
But you look...

39:54.518 --> 39:55.477
yeah.

39:55.477 --> 39:58.104
But I'm married.

39:58.104 --> 40:00.649
And I have twins--
Amy and Gemma.

40:00.649 --> 40:03.276
Oh, I remember
them well.

40:03.276 --> 40:05.779
Hello, Amy...

40:05.779 --> 40:07.113
and Gemma.

40:07.113 --> 40:08.532
That's not what I--
What?

40:08.532 --> 40:11.243
Ew!
Shit.

40:11.243 --> 40:13.745
V?

40:13.745 --> 40:15.705
That's Amy.

40:15.705 --> 40:18.542
You see that little tooth
growing there?

40:18.542 --> 40:20.252
Aw, he's so sad.

40:20.252 --> 40:22.463
Bet I could cheer him up.

40:22.463 --> 40:25.466
Dude. He's, like, 40.
He could be your dad.

40:25.466 --> 40:27.634
So? I like my dad.

40:36.477 --> 40:38.144
Hey. Hi.

40:38.144 --> 40:40.606
- Hey, you guys.
- Did you bring an extra amp?

40:40.606 --> 40:43.651
Yeah. I brought
the extra, extra amp.

40:43.651 --> 40:45.902
I thought that one
was broken.

40:45.902 --> 40:49.906
Lots of hours to fix that
on the road.

40:49.906 --> 40:52.535
So you told 'em, huh?

40:52.535 --> 40:54.495
You didn't tell
your friends?

40:54.495 --> 40:55.787
No, I did.

40:55.787 --> 40:57.581
So you got a minute?

41:01.544 --> 41:02.919
Okay.

41:02.919 --> 41:05.714
Here's what I know.

41:05.714 --> 41:08.341
You're a good guy.

41:08.341 --> 41:12.262
And I'm an asshole.
That's pretty clear.

41:12.262 --> 41:15.473
But you know how I know
I'm changing?

41:15.473 --> 41:18.977
You're a good guy, and I don't
want this to be over.

41:18.977 --> 41:22.898
I hate what I did.
I hate that I hurt you.

41:22.898 --> 41:26.527
And I want to take it back,
and I want to make it right.

41:26.527 --> 41:29.655
And I don't even know
if I really know what love is,

41:29.655 --> 41:33.825
you know, except a thing
that I fuck up all the time.

41:33.825 --> 41:36.870
But you...

41:36.870 --> 41:39.873
I respect
the shit out of you.

41:39.873 --> 41:42.083
And I miss you.

41:42.083 --> 41:44.502
And all day today
when everything in my family

41:44.502 --> 41:47.130
is just falling apart,

41:47.130 --> 41:49.758
I just kept wishing
you were with me.

41:49.758 --> 41:51.843
And that's what I know.

42:07.233 --> 42:08.902
I just need
a couple weeks.

42:08.902 --> 42:12.113
I got to get Ian settled
and get him back on his meds,

42:12.113 --> 42:14.282
cover my shifts
at the diner,

42:14.282 --> 42:16.826
but then I can come,
at least for a little while.

42:16.826 --> 42:21.498
I can help carry shit and make
sandwiches for the guys and--

42:21.498 --> 42:23.541
On--on tour?
In--in the van?

42:23.541 --> 42:27.170
[chuckles]

42:28.713 --> 42:31.049
I want to be with you.
Why is that funny?

42:31.049 --> 42:34.511
Oh, come on, you don't want
to be in the van, Fiona.

42:34.511 --> 42:37.347
It's exhausting,
and it's kind of disgusting.

42:37.347 --> 42:39.140
I mean, it's ju--

42:39.140 --> 42:43.144
it's just--it's a--
it's a bad idea.

42:43.144 --> 42:45.063
Well, I think it's
a bad idea for our marriage

42:45.063 --> 42:46.773
for us to be apart
right now.

42:46.773 --> 42:48.609
I think what was bad
for our marriage

42:48.609 --> 42:51.486
was your decision
to sleep with your ex.

42:54.740 --> 42:57.618
Listen, I-I think it's cool
that you offered,

42:57.618 --> 43:00.996
but I-I need to get out
and think a little.

43:02.580 --> 43:04.082
And you think too.
W-we'll both think.

43:04.082 --> 43:07.585
We didn't think much
before we got married, so...

43:17.345 --> 43:20.724
Will you water my plants?

43:20.724 --> 43:22.475
Okay.

43:22.475 --> 43:24.728
Thanks.

43:26.604 --> 43:29.232
I'll call you from the road.

44:01.639 --> 44:03.516
Trying to give me
shock therapy?

44:03.516 --> 44:05.435
It's supposed to be
good for you.

44:05.435 --> 44:08.980
You need to
plug it in first.

44:18.656 --> 44:19.908
Hi, I'm Dr. Thompson.

44:19.908 --> 44:21.827
Intake said
you're hallucinating?

44:21.827 --> 44:23.244
Yeah. I-I see knives.

44:23.244 --> 44:24.746
I see knives in the walls.

44:24.746 --> 44:26.832
And I want to cut myself.

44:26.832 --> 44:29.417
And I want to cut you!

44:29.417 --> 44:31.461
Have you taken
any drugs today, Debbie?

44:31.461 --> 44:33.421
- No. No.
- It's okay to tell me.

44:33.421 --> 44:36.382
I ran out. I ran out.
I need my lithium.

44:36.382 --> 44:38.802
You're 14, and you've been
diagnosed as bipolar?

44:38.802 --> 44:41.971
Yes, yes,
which is why I need my lithium.

44:41.971 --> 44:43.890
I can give you
a sedative now.

44:43.890 --> 44:46.684
Can you tell me the name of
the doctor that diagnosed you?

44:46.684 --> 44:49.604
I-I don't remember.
And I-I don't need a sedative.

44:49.604 --> 44:51.481
I need my lithium.

44:51.481 --> 44:52.816
I can't write you
for lithium

44:52.816 --> 44:54.317
without your
psychiatrist's consent.

44:54.317 --> 44:57.529
But I-I see knives.

44:57.529 --> 45:01.074
Okay. Well, do you want me
to put you on a 72-hour hold?

45:02.659 --> 45:05.370
- Like in a psych ward?
- Yeah, exactly like.

45:06.412 --> 45:08.373
[scoffs]
Fuck.

45:17.465 --> 45:19.717
- Hey, how's Ian?
- Not good.

45:19.717 --> 45:20.885
Well, what do you mean?

45:20.885 --> 45:23.763
They said
he'd just sleep for the day.

45:23.763 --> 45:26.850
[indistinct shouting]

45:28.518 --> 45:31.521
(Lip)
Hey. Hey.

45:31.521 --> 45:33.899
Hey! Hey--

45:33.899 --> 45:35.943
What's--what's
going on?

45:35.943 --> 45:37.610
My innocent son
is under arrest,

45:37.610 --> 45:38.987
thanks to your brother.

45:38.987 --> 45:41.447
- What--Ian?
- Carl!

45:41.447 --> 45:43.741
Sammi says Carl put drugs
on Chuckie.

45:43.741 --> 45:46.077
- I didn't.
- Carl, if you did that,

45:46.077 --> 45:47.788
then you--
- It's not a question of "if."

45:47.788 --> 45:50.039
There is no way that Chuckie
was smuggling heroin

45:50.039 --> 45:51.792
by himself.
- Heroin?

45:51.792 --> 45:53.585
What the fuck's
the matter with you?

45:53.585 --> 45:56.045
Carl, you have to do
the right thing

45:56.045 --> 45:57.965
and tell the cops
it was you.

45:57.965 --> 45:59.883
No, I don't.
Why would I do the right thing?

45:59.883 --> 46:03.511
Because my son is in jail,
and it is your fault!

46:03.511 --> 46:04.971
He's not going to be
in there for that long--

46:04.971 --> 46:06.472
a week maybe.
He's only ten.

46:06.472 --> 46:08.850
He's 13.

46:08.850 --> 46:10.518
He's a little small
for his age.

46:10.518 --> 46:13.730
You--you mean slow.

46:13.730 --> 46:15.983
You said "small."
But I think you meant "slow."

46:15.983 --> 46:18.109
- I meant what I said.
- Okay.

46:18.109 --> 46:22.155
Fiona? Dad?
Can I get a little backup here?

46:22.155 --> 46:24.282
Uh, best to turn
yourself in, Son.

46:24.282 --> 46:25.867
Chuckie is family
after all.

46:25.867 --> 46:27.744
Thank you.
[knock at door]

46:28.870 --> 46:30.371
(man)
Chicago Police!
Open up!

46:30.371 --> 46:33.082
- Shit!
- Oh--go, run!

46:33.082 --> 46:35.585
- Carl Gallagher?
- He ran that way.

46:35.585 --> 46:38.463
- What the fuck, Sammi?
- Sammi!

46:38.463 --> 46:39.923
- Why would--
- That's right.

46:39.923 --> 46:41.967
I told them it was Carl,

46:41.967 --> 46:43.593
and I told Chuckie
to tell them it was Carl.

46:51.309 --> 46:55.355
[sirens wailing]

46:58.900 --> 47:02.445
[sirens]

47:02.445 --> 47:04.489
[tires screech]

47:09.077 --> 47:10.703
Put your hands
in the air now!

47:10.703 --> 47:12.038
All right, don't shoot.
I'm white.

47:15.375 --> 47:19.128
[handcuffs rattling, clicking]

47:20.338 --> 47:23.341
[all singing indistinctly]

47:26.344 --> 47:29.014
[squeaking]

47:29.014 --> 47:31.724
Looks like a tough night
for the new liver.

47:31.724 --> 47:33.977
[singing continues]

47:33.977 --> 47:35.311
(several voices)
♪ If I don't get rye whiskey ♪

47:35.311 --> 47:37.730
♪ I surely will die ♪

47:37.730 --> 47:41.651
♪ Sometimes I drink whiskey,
sometimes I drink rum ♪

47:41.651 --> 47:44.862
♪ Rye whiskey, rye whiskey,
rye whiskey ♪

47:44.862 --> 47:47.657
♪ Rye whiskey ♪

47:47.657 --> 47:51.619
[several men keep singing]

47:51.619 --> 47:55.623
[shouting, overlapping chatter]

47:55.623 --> 48:00.503
[indistinct singing continues,
overlapping clamor]

48:00.503 --> 48:03.006
(men)
♪ Rye whiskey, rye whiskey ♪

48:11.848 --> 48:14.851
I think this might be
the end with Mickey--

48:14.851 --> 48:17.103
the diagnosis, you know.

48:17.103 --> 48:21.399
Even if I don't believe it,
I'm pretty sure he does.

48:21.399 --> 48:24.944
Well, if it makes you
feel any better,

48:24.944 --> 48:27.864
I already blew it
with my husband,

48:27.864 --> 48:32.618
and I don't even have any kind
of diagnosis to pin it on.

48:32.618 --> 48:34.370
Gallaghers.

48:34.370 --> 48:36.456
Gallaghers.

